Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new wireless local area network (WLAN) system that exploits physical-layer network coding (PNC) and multiuser decoding (MUD) to boost system throughput. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of network coding, specifically physical-layer network coding (PNC), to improve the throughput of the WLAN system. This involves the study of information theory concepts and techniques. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new multiple access mode called Network-Coded Multiple Access (NCMA) that allows multiple nodes to transmit simultaneously to the access point (AP) to boost throughput. This involves the design and analysis of control systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of network coding to improve the throughput of the WLAN system, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high data rates. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly discuss cryptography and security, but the proposed NCMA scheme may have implications for the security of the WLAN system, which could be a potential area of research.
